- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on out-of-domain utterance detection in intelligent assistant systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of data augmentation techniques to improve the performance of a classifier. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with intelligent assistant systems and their ability to handle noisy input. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of word embeddings, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image captioning. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve the use of neural networks for the classifier.
